      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BOOKENDS (4) sat handy last start when back to 1100m, scoring by 1.8L at Northam when jumping the $1.60 favourite. The blinkers appeared to do the trick there and the rise to 1200m is no issue. She has enough speed to offset the tricky barrier and she can go on with the job. GREAT PROMISE (1) is knocking on the door of another win, missing by 1.7L last start at Pinjarra. That effort rates highly in this field and this looks to set up nicely for her once again. Cooper's claim comes in handy and she can play a leading role once again. AJICITO (3) got across from a wide draw last start to lead and win by 0.4L at Bunbury. She'll be better for that win and a better barrier this time around suits her better. Will give them something to chase. ACQUIRED TASTE (2) flew over the top to win first-up and she makes plenty of appeal once again. CAWARRA (5) won at Kalgoorlie last start in good order and can't be left out.",
